If you&#39;re using view binding you don&#39;t need to access your components with `findViewById` method. While using view binding, pressing dot (.) after calling your view binding reference will show you all available components in your layout. You can simply use:

    btn1 = binding.button;
    btn2 = binding.button2;



But if you still want to access your components with `findViewById` method you should use it with your root view reference:

    btn1 = binding.getRoot().findViewById(R.id.button);
    btn2 = binding.getRoot().findViewById(R.id.button2);

